<br>
Robe of the elements vs Swiftclaw Sash:<br>
ok this stuff is newbie gear. no argument from me. however lets look at the effects on them. swiftclaw sash (15% melee haste) and robe of the elements (15% summoning haste). both are obtainable with a groups help in the 20's or 30's both are more than likely a newbies introduction to decent gear. however that swiftclaw sash will provide haste to the wearer thruout his lifespan. however the robe of the elements will providing its haste for the lvl 49 pets (now im not saying most or any lvl 49 mages still wear a robe of the elements just that if they did the haste would be useless).<br>
 <br>
transpose this to the endgame <br>
Grimore of Enchantment vs Dark Wind Shroud<br>
both obtainable by lvl 60's and not much lower. now that melee that was lucky enough to be awarded that shroud will be able to wear it and continue to get the haste with all his attacks. however as soon as the caster dings 61 the value of the grimore decreases. by the time that caster is 65 he/she will hardly notice the effect at all. regardless of wether or not they have found an upgrade. <br>
<br>
Now lets look at something like weapon procs. we could equate weapon procs with improved damage. since they amount to the same thing basically. lets say a pair of lvl 35's 1 with a venomous axe of the velium brood(75dd poison proc) and another with a wurm scale coat (Improved dmg 2)<br>
<br>
now that melee can use that weapon his entire lifespan and still get the 75dd proc ( granted he will most likely replace the weapon later) but he could bank it and use it for cr's and still count on the weapon to proc. however the wurmscale coat will not add damage to lvl 49 spells. <br>
<br>
<br>
my question is this why does caster gear have a FIXED end of life. why or more correclty why is caster gear the only gear with a fixed end of life. a cloak of flames is just as good with a rusty longsword as with a bloodbath. <br>
<br>
as melee's progress they get better gear along the way. haste gets better or the items with haste get better as they progress. starting with the swiftclaw sash and workin up to darkwind shroud(or insert other haste gear you like here) but if they dont they can still rely on thier old gear to fuction as it has since they got it.  <br>
<br>
<br>
focused shock of feiry blades using vt/ntov 3.7 dmg per mana<br>
vs sunvortex with the same gear. unfocused 3.25 dmg per mana <br>
call me strange but shouldnt the reward for hunting in VT be useable for more than one level as a caster. or the focus effect work at all if you go after lvl 60. <br>
<br>
<br>
