<br>
It would have been a much better choise to have foci levels scale in percentages instead of usable levels:<br>
<br>
Lvl 1 damage focus gives 1-5% to all nukes and works for all levels and a lvl 3 damage focus gives 1-15% to all nukes.<br>
<br>
Not only does this give better options for higher level loot (VT drop gives focus 5 for instance which increases damage with 1-25%) but also doesn't make certain items totally obsolete after you ding. <br>
Maybe even some higher foci will have minimum levels at which it will work to prevent twinking.<br>
<br>
Everything else in the game uses that system (FT, haste, procs, ANY effect), why not foci? <br>
A level 49+ caster's most efficient spells will be his level 44 ones if he can't get his hand on the more rare level 3 focus items.<br>
<br>
<br>
